Function.Name: Stretch
Function.Description: Enhances an image by adjusting the range of values displayed. This does not alter the underlying pixel values. If a pixel has a value outside of the specified range, it will appear as either the minimum or maximum value.

Function.Name: Extract VV Band
Function.Description: Specifies which bands to work with when using multiband datasets.

AnyType.Help: This raster function extracts the VV band (band 1). Values are displayed in dB scale (converted from amplitude scale).

RasterFunctionTemplate.Help: This raster function extracts the VV band (band 1). Values are displayed with a MinMax stretch applied (-30 to 0) based on dB scale values (converted from amplitude scale). To work with RTC pixel values, select one of the templates that does not include a stretch setting.
